HEADWORD: Dimera
<hw>Dim"e*ra</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<grk>di-</grk> = <grk>di`s-</grk> twice + <?/ part.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A division of Coleoptera, having
two joints to the tarsi.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A division of the
Hemiptera, including the aphids.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dimeran</ent>⟦br⟧
